docs.abstract: Letchworth State Park: Article on 14,34-acre Letchworth State Park, which is divided by 17-mi-long canyon and is site of Genesee River Gorge; park is open to public yr-round but is primarily arboretum and wildlife sanctuary; land was originally owned by William Pryor Letchworth, who deeded it to NYS in 1910 for use as park under supervision of Amer Scenic and Historic Preservation Soc; scenic features of park described; advice and routes and facilities; map; illus of gorge (L)
